WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:04.046
<i>( music playing )</i>

00:30.364 --> 00:32.282
<i>( cell phone ringing )</i>

00:35.244 --> 00:37.204
‐ <i>( ringing )</i>
‐ Ohh.

00:40.415 --> 00:42.417
Hey. ( laughs )

00:42.501 --> 00:45.629
No. My flight was canceled.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.798
Now I'm gonna
have to stay overnight.

00:47.881 --> 00:51.093
Well, just tell Roderick
not to worry, OK?

00:51.176 --> 00:53.512
I sent the specimen
via charter,

00:53.595 --> 00:55.639
they should be
getting there tomorrow.

00:55.722 --> 00:59.184
Yeah, no, I think the investors
are gonna be really thrilled.

00:59.268 --> 01:01.603
We got some great additions
for the new wing.

01:03.105 --> 01:06.108
Well, he <i>should</i> be happy.

01:06.191 --> 01:09.027
Yes, he should think
it's worth it, because I don't‐‐

01:09.111 --> 01:10.946
( sighs ) Yeah. That's fine.

01:11.029 --> 01:12.823
I'm just exhausted.

01:12.906 --> 01:17.202
Finally had a shower, though,
and that was heaven. ( laughs )

01:17.286 --> 01:21.039
<i>No, I'm just tired</i>
<i>of the same old thing.</i>

01:21.123 --> 01:22.708
<i>The investors</i>
<i>will be pleased,</i>

01:22.791 --> 01:25.294
<i>I just wanted to find</i>
<i>something special...</i>

01:28.422 --> 01:32.384
<i>Yeah, I'll take some time off</i>
<i>and we can finally...</i>

01:32.467 --> 01:34.428
<i>( continues, indistinct )</i>

01:38.557 --> 01:40.976
<i>( continues talking,</i>
<i>indistinct )</i>

01:42.686 --> 01:44.229
<i>Just hold them off</i>
<i>until I get there,</i>

01:44.313 --> 01:47.482
<i>and no, I don't trust you.</i>
<i>OK? Bye.</i>

01:56.283 --> 01:58.160
( lightly snoring )

02:02.497 --> 02:03.665
Mmm.

02:07.336 --> 02:08.629
Hmm.

02:13.967 --> 02:15.969
<i>OK. Huh‐‐</i>

02:17.554 --> 02:19.222
( whimpers )

02:22.309 --> 02:23.477
What‐‐

02:25.854 --> 02:28.690
( panting )

03:31.586 --> 03:33.755
( panting )

03:39.845 --> 03:41.847
‐ ( thud )
‐ Ow.

03:41.930 --> 03:43.265
Ow.

03:45.934 --> 03:47.602
( grunts )

03:56.111 --> 03:57.320
( sniffs )

03:59.364 --> 04:00.449
Hmm.

04:19.551 --> 04:21.344
Holy shit.

04:24.639 --> 04:26.850
( laughing )

04:30.645 --> 04:32.606
Oh, my God.

04:32.689 --> 04:35.317
( laughing )

04:38.445 --> 04:39.488
<i>( phone ringing )</i>

04:41.239 --> 04:43.200
<i>( ringing )</i>

04:45.076 --> 04:46.828
<i>( ringing )</i>

04:48.371 --> 04:49.956
<i>( ringing )</i>

04:54.252 --> 04:55.921
Hello?

04:56.004 --> 04:58.089
Oh. Right.

04:58.173 --> 04:59.591
Wake‐up call.

04:59.674 --> 05:01.384
Um, actually,

05:01.468 --> 05:04.346
I‐I'm not gonna be
checking out today.

05:04.429 --> 05:06.973
Ah... Well, I'm not sure.

05:07.057 --> 05:09.017
How‐‐ How long
can you give me?

05:10.477 --> 05:12.395
The what? The Ren Faire?

05:12.479 --> 05:14.940
People actually come for that?

05:15.023 --> 05:16.274
Uh‐huh.

05:16.358 --> 05:17.776
Yeah, no, I understand.

05:17.859 --> 05:19.277
Yeah. OK.

05:19.361 --> 05:20.987
Yeah. One week. Got it.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.092
( gasps )

05:47.222 --> 05:49.057
What are you?

05:49.140 --> 05:50.725
( camera clicks )

05:52.769 --> 05:54.688
<i>( line out ringing )</i>

05:54.771 --> 05:56.147
Man:
<i>Hey. You almost here?</i>

05:56.231 --> 05:58.692
Uh, actually,
I'm gonna be a bit longer.

05:58.775 --> 06:01.570
‐ <i>What? Why?</i>
‐ I think I found something.

06:01.653 --> 06:03.071
<i>On your layover?</i>

06:03.154 --> 06:05.490
Or it found me, but yeah. Kinda.

06:05.574 --> 06:07.158
<i>What am I supposed</i>
<i>to tell Roderick</i>
<i>and the investors?</i>

06:07.242 --> 06:08.827
<i>Everyone came in</i>
<i>on the weekend.</i>

06:08.910 --> 06:10.996
Well, tell them this
is more important than the wing.

06:11.079 --> 06:13.582
‐ <i>What do you mean?</i>
‐ I'm not entirely sure yet,

06:13.665 --> 06:15.500
but I think maybe...

06:15.584 --> 06:20.171
( laughs ) Honestly,
I have no idea what it is.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.465
Hey, have my specimen
arrived yet?

06:22.549 --> 06:24.509
<i>Yes, and we desperately</i>
<i>need your help</i>

06:24.593 --> 06:26.595
<i>in deciphering</i>
<i>your shitty handwriting.</i>

06:26.678 --> 06:29.514
OK. Do me a favor.
Look at the crates
that they came in.

06:29.598 --> 06:33.184
We're looking for pollen grains,
red‐orange in color.

06:33.268 --> 06:35.520
I'm gonna send you
a picture now.

06:35.604 --> 06:38.356
Found some remnants
on my clothing.

06:38.440 --> 06:39.816
I don't know how I missed this,

06:39.899 --> 06:42.360
but I seem to have
brought some back with me.

06:42.444 --> 06:45.238
It's the only thing I can think
of that would explain‐‐

06:46.823 --> 06:48.116
( breathing heavily )

06:48.199 --> 06:50.869
Male Vocalist:
<i>♪ Who do you suppose ♪</i>

06:50.952 --> 06:54.748
<i>♪ I really love? ♪</i>

06:56.583 --> 06:59.044
<i>♪ Who do you suppose ♪</i>

06:59.127 --> 07:02.797
<i>♪ I'm thinking of? ♪</i>

07:04.466 --> 07:07.135
<i>‐ ♪ Who do you suppose ♪</i>
<i>‐ ( cell phone ringing )</i>

07:07.218 --> 07:09.888
<i>♪ I dream of ♪</i>

07:09.971 --> 07:11.848
<i>♪ Both day and night? ♪</i>

07:11.931 --> 07:15.060
<i>‐ ( ringing )</i>
<i>‐ ♪ And whose loving arms ♪</i>

07:15.143 --> 07:17.646
<i>♪ I need ♪</i>

07:17.729 --> 07:20.482
<i>‐ ♪ To hold me tight? ♪</i>
<i>‐ ( camera clicks )</i>

07:20.565 --> 07:23.026
<i>♪ Everybody knows ♪</i>

07:23.109 --> 07:26.988
<i>♪ I'm hypnotized ♪</i>

07:28.281 --> 07:31.076
<i>♪ Every time I look ♪</i>

07:31.159 --> 07:35.163
<i>♪ Right into your eyes ♪</i>

07:36.873 --> 07:38.416
<i>♪ Who do you suppose ♪</i>

07:38.500 --> 07:40.627
<i>♪ I'll always miss ♪</i>

07:40.710 --> 07:44.422
<i>♪ Whose lips</i>
<i>I love to kiss ♪</i>

07:44.506 --> 07:47.384
<i>♪ Who do you suppose? ♪</i>

07:47.467 --> 07:51.554
<i>♪ Dear, it's you ♪</i>

08:05.110 --> 08:06.528
‐ ( sniffs )
‐ Ohh.

08:21.751 --> 08:22.711
( zips bag )

08:41.771 --> 08:42.731
Mm.

08:48.028 --> 08:49.779
‐ <i>( knocking on door )</i>
‐ Woman: <i>Housekeeping.</i>

08:49.863 --> 08:52.157
No. No, no, no, no.
Hold on, hold on. No.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.534
‐ Do not disturb.
‐ <i>What in God's name?</i>

08:54.617 --> 08:56.703
<i>Is everything OK in there?</i>

08:56.786 --> 08:59.080
Thank you. I'm fine.

09:00.415 --> 09:03.626
<i>( housekeeping cart</i>
<i>rumbles away )</i>

09:07.922 --> 09:09.424
( sighs )

09:16.890 --> 09:17.932
( sighs )

09:23.271 --> 09:25.774
( shower faucet squeaks )

09:26.941 --> 09:28.318
Come on.

09:37.619 --> 09:38.953
( gasps )

09:49.464 --> 09:50.882
( camera clicking )

09:50.965 --> 09:53.968
<i>( splashing )</i>

10:03.853 --> 10:05.313
( phone beeps )

10:09.734 --> 10:11.945
Oh‐‐ Shit.

10:12.028 --> 10:15.573
( breathing heavily )

10:15.657 --> 10:17.700
Text Joe.

10:17.784 --> 10:20.620
Joe. Joe, check this out.
I can't ID‐‐

10:20.703 --> 10:24.749
I've never seen
anything like it before.

10:24.833 --> 10:29.170
There's an entire ecosystem
growing before my eyes.

10:29.254 --> 10:30.171
( beeps )

10:34.217 --> 10:36.177
‐ Hey.
‐ <i>( text alert )</i>

10:39.681 --> 10:42.350
<i>( chuckles )</i>

10:56.364 --> 10:58.199
<i>( knocking on door )</i>

11:03.788 --> 11:05.290
<i>( knocking )</i>

11:05.373 --> 11:07.333
Oh, fuck, not again.

11:10.628 --> 11:12.630
( rattling )

11:12.714 --> 11:16.050
‐ Coming!
‐ What's going on in there?!

11:16.134 --> 11:17.969
Sir. Sir. Sir, sir.

11:18.052 --> 11:20.305
My name is Dr. Merian Wallace.

11:20.388 --> 11:23.057
No, I'm‐‐ I'm a scientist, OK?

11:23.141 --> 11:26.269
What we have in this room
is a phenomenon,

11:26.352 --> 11:28.605
‐ a major scientific discovery.
‐ Open the door.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.607
No, sir, I cannot do that.
I can't let you in here.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.860
‐ I need to continue
my field research.
‐ ( grunts )

11:33.943 --> 11:36.821
What on God's earth
did you do to this room?!

11:36.905 --> 11:38.698
Nothing. I've done nothing.

11:38.781 --> 11:41.326
I may have trailed in
a bit of pollen,

11:41.409 --> 11:43.077
but it's what the room did.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.663
If you don't open this door,
I'm gonna call the police.

11:45.747 --> 11:47.957
‐ No. The police are not
gonna know what this is.
‐ <i>( cell phone ringing )</i>

11:48.041 --> 11:52.545
OK, look, I want you
and your‐‐ your plants
out of my motel <i>now.</i>

11:52.629 --> 11:54.172
You said that I had a week.

11:54.255 --> 11:56.507
Well, the maid said something
fishy was going on in here.

11:56.591 --> 11:59.636
We don't tolerate vandalism,
and you're gonna have to pay
for all that damage.

11:59.719 --> 12:00.595
Look, listen to me.

12:00.678 --> 12:02.096
If this is about money,

12:02.180 --> 12:05.016
I have investors who will pay
to preserve this.

12:05.099 --> 12:07.769
‐ <i>( cell phone ringing )</i>
‐ This is my colleague, Joe.

12:07.852 --> 12:10.355
I'm gonna put him on,
and he's gonna confirm that.
Joe?

12:10.438 --> 12:12.982
<i>Merian, I have been</i>
<i>trying to get ahold of you.</i>

12:13.066 --> 12:15.318
<i>Do you have any idea</i>
<i>what we have on our hands?</i>

12:15.401 --> 12:18.363
‐ Tell me.
‐ <i>The images and recordings</i>
<i>you're sending me, Merian,</i>

12:18.446 --> 12:21.741
<i>I've checked over</i>
<i>and over again,</i>
<i>and across the board,</i>

12:21.824 --> 12:26.955
<i>I'm finding consistent proof,</i>
<i>spanning all of the species</i>
<i>you are presenting.</i>

12:27.038 --> 12:28.498
Proof of what?

12:28.581 --> 12:31.209
<i>Everything in that room</i>
<i>exhibits characteristics</i>

12:31.292 --> 12:34.379
<i>that mimic archaic species.</i>

12:34.462 --> 12:36.214
‐ ( panting )
‐ Manager: What's he saying?

12:36.297 --> 12:38.091
‐ <i>Who is that?</i>
‐ Don't worry.

12:38.174 --> 12:40.093
Are‐Are you saying that‐‐

12:40.176 --> 12:42.262
<i>I believe the ecosystem</i>
<i>you are experiencing</i>

12:42.345 --> 12:45.974
<i>is supporting</i>
<i>the reintroduction of</i>
<i>long‐extinct life.</i>

12:48.935 --> 12:51.604
I‐‐ Say that again?

12:51.688 --> 12:55.608
<i>Somehow this habitat</i>
<i>has brought species</i>
<i>back to life.</i>

12:57.151 --> 12:59.654
‐ <i>Did you hear me?</i>
‐ Yeah, I hear you.

12:59.737 --> 13:03.408
<i>Look, I've tested similar</i>
<i>pollen that we found on</i>
<i>the crates, as you asked,</i>

13:03.491 --> 13:08.037
<i>with no results,</i>
<i>but there</i> is <i>something about</i>
<i>the components of that room</i>

13:08.121 --> 13:10.164
<i>that is allowing this system</i>
<i>to flourish.</i>

13:10.248 --> 13:12.083
<i>Merian, you could be</i>
<i>at the center</i>

13:12.166 --> 13:14.877
<i>of the biggest</i>
<i>scientific discovery</i>
<i>of our time.</i>

13:14.961 --> 13:17.964
‐ <i>We have to tell Roderick.</i>
‐ No.

13:18.047 --> 13:20.425
Joe, I gotta call you back.

13:20.508 --> 13:25.471
Sir, listen, I work for a very
heavily backed natural history
museum and trust.

13:25.555 --> 13:30.268
You give me some more time
in here, I promise that you
will be compensated heavily.

13:30.351 --> 13:32.770
‐ How much?
‐ Well‐‐

13:32.854 --> 13:35.064
I need somethin'.

13:35.148 --> 13:36.941
Um...

13:37.025 --> 13:39.277
Uh, listen, I have, um...

13:39.360 --> 13:41.279
Here. Take‐‐

13:41.362 --> 13:45.116
What, four bucks?
And some weird foreign money
I can't do anything with?

13:45.199 --> 13:46.784
All right. Here.
Try running this.

13:46.868 --> 13:47.869
What‐‐

13:47.952 --> 13:49.287
Take it all, then.

13:49.370 --> 13:51.289
I'm sorry, but please,
you have to help me.

13:51.372 --> 13:53.833
No, listen to me!
This is <i>very</i> important!

13:53.916 --> 13:56.627
You have to help me, OK?
You have to help me.

13:56.711 --> 13:59.797
I'll get you whatever you want.
I'll get you whatever you want.

13:59.881 --> 14:02.175
OK? Please.
( crying ) You just‐‐

14:02.258 --> 14:05.553
My keys. Take my keys.
It's a really nice car.

14:05.636 --> 14:07.138
I'll get it up to you
somehow, OK?

14:07.221 --> 14:10.224
OK! OK. You can have
till the rest of the week.

14:11.434 --> 14:13.102
Thank you. Wait. Sir.

14:13.186 --> 14:15.188
I have to ask one more thing.

14:16.272 --> 14:18.232
We keep this between us.

14:18.316 --> 14:20.485
Why? What‐‐

14:20.568 --> 14:22.570
We have to keep it safe.

14:27.742 --> 14:29.410
<i>( crickets chirping )</i>

14:34.499 --> 14:37.001
Tiny geniuses.

14:37.085 --> 14:38.086
<i>( cell phone ringing )</i>

14:38.169 --> 14:41.089
‐ ( thud )
‐ Ow. Jeez.

14:41.172 --> 14:43.841
‐ Hey.
‐ Joe: <i>Merian, you OK?</i>

14:43.925 --> 14:46.511
( laughs ) Yeah. I'm great.

14:46.594 --> 14:48.221
The best.

14:48.304 --> 14:50.223
God, Joe, I wish
you were here to see this.

14:50.306 --> 14:53.267
<i>I know. You get the fun part of</i>
<i>the job, seein' things alive.</i>

14:53.351 --> 14:56.187
<i>Speakin' of which, I'm gonna</i>
<i>need another specimen.</i>

14:56.270 --> 14:57.772
Why, what happened
to the one I sent?

14:57.855 --> 14:59.482
‐ <i>It was DOA.</i>
‐ What?!

14:59.565 --> 15:02.860
Joe, do you know
what I had to go through
to get that to you?

15:02.944 --> 15:04.529
<i>Just send another.</i>

15:04.612 --> 15:06.531
No. Joe, I don't have
any of my equipment here

15:06.614 --> 15:08.866
to do proper research, OK?
And I can't leave.

15:08.950 --> 15:11.410
I even had to give the maid
my expedition windbreaker

15:11.494 --> 15:12.829
just to go to FedEx for me.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.372
<i>But Roderick's</i>
<i>gonna need proof!</i>

15:14.455 --> 15:16.415
Joe, I don't know
what to tell you, OK?

15:16.499 --> 15:17.542
I've sent photos.

15:17.625 --> 15:19.252
The pollen didn't react for you,

15:19.335 --> 15:21.712
‐ my specimen didn't survive.
‐ <i>Merian‐‐</i>

15:21.796 --> 15:24.132
I'm not taking
any more chances, OK?

15:24.215 --> 15:27.468
These species, they don't exist
anywhere else. This is it.

15:27.552 --> 15:30.388
This is the only place,
and now I'm even doubting

15:30.471 --> 15:33.891
if they're gonna survive
if I take them out of this room.

15:33.975 --> 15:36.519
Until I know for sure, I'm‐‐

15:36.602 --> 15:39.063
I don't want to
take them out of here.

15:39.147 --> 15:41.899
<i>Then what's your plan?</i>

15:41.983 --> 15:44.527
( stammers )
To study. To learn.

15:44.610 --> 15:48.197
<i>But I mean, like, what,</i>
<i>are you just gonna</i>
<i>stay there forever?</i>

15:48.281 --> 15:51.534
<i>You haven't even</i>
<i>left the room.</i>

15:51.617 --> 15:54.120
‐ ( scoffs )
‐ <i>Merian, I'm worried about you.</i>

15:54.203 --> 15:57.582
<i>I can't help you if I don't</i>
<i>know what we're dealing with.</i>

15:57.665 --> 16:00.585
<i>Will you please,</i>
<i>for the love of God,</i>
<i>call your husband?</i>

16:00.668 --> 16:03.045
<i>He's freaking the fuck out.</i>

16:09.510 --> 16:11.888
( sighs )

16:11.971 --> 16:15.016
Morning, <i>Magna fugatura.</i>

16:15.099 --> 16:18.728
Oh, good morning,
<i>Fem asinuscaudu Merianema.</i>

16:18.811 --> 16:21.480
Morning, <i>Vinea Franklyn.</i>

16:25.026 --> 16:27.028
<i>( cell phone ringing )</i>

16:30.198 --> 16:32.283
‐ Hey, Joe.
‐ <i>I'm so sorry.</i>

16:32.366 --> 16:35.453
‐ About what?
‐ <i>You were starting</i>
<i>to scare me yesterday</i>

16:35.536 --> 16:37.955
<i>talking like you</i>
<i>might not come home,</i>
<i>and I had to‐‐</i>

16:38.039 --> 16:39.874
<i>It's the INH Museum</i>
<i>Code of Ethics‐‐</i>

16:39.957 --> 16:42.084
<i>we don't really know</i>
<i>what we're dealing with.</i>

16:42.168 --> 16:43.544
Wait, what are you
talking about?

16:43.628 --> 16:45.296
<i>And you haven't</i>
<i>even called Andy.</i>

16:45.379 --> 16:47.465
<i>What if you've been</i>
<i>infected with something?</i>

16:47.548 --> 16:48.758
<i>This is insane.</i>

16:48.841 --> 16:50.301
<i>Not to mention</i>
<i>the rate of growth</i>

16:50.384 --> 16:53.137
‐ <i>and patterns that‐‐</i>
‐ Joe, what did you do?

16:53.221 --> 16:55.806
<i>I had to tell Roderick,</i>
<i>and he gave them everything,</i>

16:55.890 --> 16:58.017
<i>not just the pollen,</i>
<i>but everything.</i>

16:58.100 --> 16:59.810
<i>And they quarantined our lab‐‐</i>

16:59.894 --> 17:01.354
Joe, who is coming?

17:01.437 --> 17:03.648
<i>‐ ( banging on door )</i>
<i>‐</i> Man: <i>NIASDI, open up!</i>

17:03.731 --> 17:05.983
Joe:
<i>You have to believe me,</i>
<i>I did this for you.</i>

17:06.067 --> 17:09.070
Man: <i>The National Invasive</i>
<i>& Alien Species Department</i>
<i>of the Interior!</i>

17:09.153 --> 17:11.697
<i>We have reason to believe you</i>
<i>are harboring invasive species</i>

17:11.781 --> 17:13.616
<i>foreign to the US</i>
<i>and possibly threatening!</i>

17:13.699 --> 17:14.992
Joe:
<i>Just do what they say, Merian.</i>

17:15.076 --> 17:18.037
What?! No!
They'll take everything!

17:18.120 --> 17:20.414
<i>Merian, it's the government.</i>

17:20.498 --> 17:23.584
‐ Joe, they'll destroy it.
‐ <i>I know.</i>

17:23.668 --> 17:26.003
<i>‐ ( banging on door )</i>
<i>‐</i> Man: <i>Mrs. Wallace, open up!</i>

17:26.087 --> 17:27.547
<i>This is a matter</i>
<i>of national security!</i>

17:27.630 --> 17:29.882
Fuck you!
And it's <i>Dr.</i> Wallace!

17:29.966 --> 17:33.010
‐ Joe: <i>Merian, no. Merian‐‐</i>
‐ Fuck you too, Joe.
You don't care.

17:33.094 --> 17:35.346
Man:
<i>Dr. Wallace,</i>
<i>we do not want to hurt you,</i>

17:35.429 --> 17:37.139
<i>but if you don't cooperate,</i>

17:37.223 --> 17:39.350
<i>we will be forced to treat you</i>
<i>as a terrorist.</i>

